{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/subscriptions/openaisub","identifier":"Options","question":"When Options.Path is empty for Login, LogoutWithOptions, or CheckStatusWithOptions, what credential file path is used?","answer":"When `Options.Path` is empty, all three operations use:\n\n`DefaultPath()` -\u003e `cascade.ExpandPath(\"~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json\")`\n\nSo the credential file is:\n\n`~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json`, expanded to an absolute path under the current user’s home directory.\n\nEvidence:\n- `Login` calls `authPath(opts.Options)` before saving credentials.\n- `LogoutWithOptions` removes `authPath(opts)`.\n- `CheckStatusWithOptions` calls `loadAuth(opts)`, which reads from `authPath(opts)`.\n- `authPath` returns `DefaultPath()` when `opts.Path == \"\"`.\n- `DefaultPath` returns `cascade.ExpandPath(\"~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json\")`.\n\nThe package spec also documents: “Stores auth in `~/.codalotl/openai_auth.json` by default.”"}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1779753078,"paths":["internal/subscriptions/openaisub/SPEC.md","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub.go","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"be1277d6c54416b3eb74669488e25b931036bd1a","git_merge_base":"92686e8927e891ac21e42a7b11adc0931a0d703f"}}